---
title: Poppin’ Jalapeño Turkey Stuffed Peppers with Cheddar & Sour Cream
description: A comfort food classic, these stuffed peppers get a kick from our bold Southwest spice blend and quick-pickled jalapeños. Bell peppers are stuffed with a creamy rice and pork filling, then smothered with cheddar cheese and baked until browned and bubbling. A final dollop of sour cream is all that’s needed for these crowd-pleasing favorites.
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/666862f6223895220f19805c-083720a5.jpeg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/6669dd79223895220f198c00-en-US.pdf
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/poppin-jalapeno-turkey-stuffed-peppers-6669dd79223895220f198c00
time required: 35 minutes
cuisine: North America
author: Sara Heilman
nutrition:
  calories: 1040 kcal
  fat: 58 g
  saturated fat: 24 g
  carbohydrates: 80 g
  sugar: 9 g
  protein: 43 g
  fiber: 3 g
  sodium: 980 mg
course: main course
servings: 2
---

Adjust rack to top position and preheat oven to 425 degrees. Wash and dry produce.

Halve, peel, and thinly slice @jalapeño{2}(halved, peeled, and thinly sliced) (remove ribs and seeds for less heat). Halve @green bell pepper{2} lengthwise; remove stems and seeds.

In a #small microwave-safe bowl{}, combine jalapeños, @white wine vinegar{5%tsp}, @sugar{1/4%tsp} (1/2 tsp for 4 servings), and a pinch of @salt{pinch}. Cover tightly with #plastic wrap{} and microwave for ~{1%minute}. Set aside to pickle, stirring occasionally.

In a #small pot{}, combine @jasmine rice{3/4%cup}, 1¼ cups water (2¼ cups for 4 servings), and a pinch of @salt{pinch}. Bring to a boil, then cover and reduce to a low simmer. Cook until rice is tender, ~{15-18%minutes}.

Keep covered off heat until ready to use in Step 5.

While rice cooks, place bell peppers on a #baking sheet{} and drizzle each half with @cooking oil{5%tsp}; rub to coat. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Arrange cut sides down.

Roast on top rack until browned and softened, ~{15-18%minutes}.

Meanwhile, heat a drizzle of oil in a large, preferably ovenproof, pan over medium-high heat. Add @ground turkey{10%oz} and season with @southwest spice blend{1%tbsp}, salt, and pepper. Cook, breaking up meat into pieces, until browned and cooked through, ~{4-6%minutes}.

> Swap in beef or turkey for pork.

Stir in @veggie stock concentrate{2}, @cream cheese{1/2%cup}, and 1/3 cup water (1/2 cup for 4 servings). Reduce heat to medium low and cook until mixture has slightly thickened, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Fluff rice with a #fork{}; stir in @butter{1%tbsp} (2 TBSP for 4 servings).

Stir rice and half the pickled jalapeños and their liquid into pan with filling until thoroughly combined; season with salt and pepper to taste.

Once bell peppers are done, remove from oven. Carefully flip and stuff pepper halves with as much filling as will fit (save the rest for serving).

Transfer stuffed peppers to pan with remaining filling. (If your pan isn't ovenproof, transfer stuffed peppers and remaining filling to a #baking dish{} now.) Evenly sprinkle with @cheddar cheese{1/2%cup}. Bake on top rack until cheese melts, ~{4-5%minutes}.

Divide remaining filling between plates. Top with stuffed peppers and as many remaining pickled jalapeños (draining first) as you like. Dollop with @sour cream{1.5%tbsp} and serve.

> Ground Turkey is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 165°.